cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper deals with natural language processing and the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for sequence modeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the behavior and learning of RNNs, which falls under the scope of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of LSTM models also suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a category. Finally, the paper uses controlled psycholinguistic experimentation, which could fall under the scope of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
